---
import CodexLayout from "../../layouts/CodexLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/quickstart-shared.css";
---

<CodexLayout
  title="Codex CLI Quickstart — Up and Running in 10 Minutes"
  description="Install Codex CLI, point it at your codebase, and run your first autonomous coding task in under 10 minutes."
  currentPage="quickstart"
>
  <div class="qs-wrapper">

    <header class="qs-hero">
      <span class="qs-hero__eyebrow">Codex CLI · Getting Started</span>
      <h1 class="qs-hero__title">
        Quick<span class="qs-hero__accent">Start</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="qs-hero__desc">OpenAI's autonomous coding agent. Reads your repo, writes code, runs commands. Built for unattended runs and CI automation.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="qs-journey">

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">01</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Prerequisites</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Node.js 18+ and OpenAI API key</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Get your API key from platform.openai.com. Then set it in your shell.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>export OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...</code></div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Add it to your .zshrc or .bashrc so it persists across sessions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">02</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Install</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Install the Codex CLI globally</h2>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>npm install -g @openai/codex</code></div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Verify: codex --version</p>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">03</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">First Run</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Launch in your project</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Navigate to your repo and launch Codex. It reads your files and waits for instructions.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd-group">
          <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>cd your-project</code></div>
          <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>codex</code></div>
        </div>
        <p class="qs-cmd-note">Interactive mode. Type your task. Codex reads the relevant files and proposes changes with your approval.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="qs-step qs-step--active">
        <div class="qs-step__dot">04</div>
        <span class="qs-step__label">Try it</span>
        <h2 class="qs-step__title">Your first real task</h2>
        <p class="qs-step__desc">Give it a concrete, scoped task. The --approval-mode suggest flag means it will show you changes before applying them.</p>
        <div class="qs-cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>codex "add input validation to the login form" --approval-mode suggest</code></div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="qs-milestone">
      <span class="qs-milestone__eyebrow">First Real Task</span>
      <h2 class="qs-milestone__title">Create .codex/instructions.md — your persistent context</h2>
      <p class="qs-milestone__desc">This is the single most impactful thing you can do. Codex reads this file at the start of every run. Put your project conventions, stack details, and any do's and don'ts here.</p>
      <div class="qs-milestone__steps">
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">1</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Create the directory and file in your project root.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="qs-milestone__cmd"><code><span class="qs-cmd__prompt">$</span>mkdir -p .codex && touch .codex/instructions.md</code></div>
      <div class="qs-milestone__steps">
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">2</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Add your stack, conventions, and rules. Example: "This is a Next.js 14 app. Use TypeScript, never any. Prefer server components. Tests go in __tests__/ next to the source file."</div>
        </div>
        <div class="qs-milestone__step">
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-num">3</div>
          <div class="qs-milestone__step-body">Codex reads it automatically. Every future run starts informed.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="qs-next">
      <p class="qs-next__title">What next?</p>
      <div class="qs-next__grid">
        <a href="/codex-cli/tips/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">⚡</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Tips & Tricks</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Approval modes, exec mode, sub-agents, CI patterns.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/codex-cli/cheatsheet/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">📋</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Cheatsheet</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">All flags and workflows at a glance.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/codex-cli/changelog/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">🔔</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Changelog</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Every Codex release, tracked.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/codex-cli/configs/" class="qs-next__card">
          <span class="qs-next__card-arrow">⚙️</span>
          <div class="qs-next__card-title">Configs</div>
          <p class="qs-next__card-desc">Full configuration reference.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.querySelectorAll('.qs-cmd').forEach(function(block) {
      var btn = document.createElement('button');
      btn.className = 'qs-cmd__copy';
      btn.textContent = 'copy';
      btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
        var code = block.querySelector('code');
        if (!code) return;
        var text = code.textContent.replace(/^\$\s*/, '').trim();
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(function() {
          btn.textContent = 'copied!';
          setTimeout(function() { btn.textContent = 'copy'; }, 1500);
        });
      });
      block.style.paddingRight = '5rem';
      block.appendChild(btn);
    });
  </script>
</CodexLayout>
